sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Middleware as BearerToken Middleware
    participant Validator as TokenValidator (adapter)
    participant JWTManager as jwt.Manager
    participant GolangJWT as golang-jwt/jwt/v5
    participant Handler as HTTP Handler

    Note over Client,Handler: JWT Authentication Flow

    Client->>Middleware: HTTP Request<br/>Authorization: Bearer <token>

    Middleware->>Middleware: Extract Authorization header
    alt Missing header
        Middleware-->>Client: 401 {"error":"missing authorization header"}
    end

    Middleware->>Middleware: Validate "Bearer " prefix
    alt Invalid scheme
        Middleware-->>Client: 401 {"error":"invalid authorization scheme, expected Bearer"}
    end

    Middleware->>Middleware: Extract token string
    alt Empty token
        Middleware-->>Client: 401 {"error":"empty bearer token"}
    end

    Middleware->>Validator: ValidateToken(tokenStr)
    Validator->>JWTManager: Validate(tokenStr)

    JWTManager->>GolangJWT: Parse(tokenStr, keyFunc)
    GolangJWT->>GolangJWT: Decode header and payload
    GolangJWT->>GolangJWT: Verify signature with secret

    alt Signing method mismatch
        GolangJWT-->>JWTManager: error: unexpected signing method
        JWTManager-->>Validator: error: failed to parse token
        Validator-->>Middleware: error
        Middleware-->>Client: 401 {"error":"invalid token"}
    end

    alt Token expired or invalid
        GolangJWT-->>JWTManager: error: token expired/invalid
        JWTManager-->>Validator: error: failed to parse token
        Validator-->>Middleware: error
        Middleware-->>Client: 401 {"error":"invalid token"}
    end

    GolangJWT-->>JWTManager: parsed token with MapClaims

    JWTManager->>JWTManager: Extract claims map
    JWTManager->>JWTManager: Parse exp -> ExpiresAt
    JWTManager->>JWTManager: Parse iat -> IssuedAt
    JWTManager-->>Validator: *jwt.Token{Claims, ExpiresAt, IssuedAt, Raw}

    Validator->>Validator: Extract Claims map
    Validator-->>Middleware: claims map[string]interface{}

    Middleware->>Middleware: Store claims in context (ClaimsKey)
    Middleware->>Middleware: Extract scopes from claims if present
    Middleware->>Middleware: Store scopes in context (ScopesKey)

    Middleware->>Handler: next.ServeHTTP(w, r.WithContext(ctx))

    Handler->>Handler: ClaimsFromContext(ctx) -> claims
    Handler->>Handler: ScopesFromContext(ctx) -> scopes
    Handler->>Handler: Process request

    Handler-->>Client: HTTP Response

    Note over Client,Handler: Token Refresh Flow

    Client->>JWTManager: Refresh(oldTokenStr)
    JWTManager->>JWTManager: Validate(oldTokenStr)
    alt Invalid token
        JWTManager-->>Client: error: cannot refresh invalid token
    end
    JWTManager->>JWTManager: Strip exp, iat, iss from claims
    JWTManager->>JWTManager: Create(userClaims)
    JWTManager->>GolangJWT: NewWithClaims + SignedString
    GolangJWT-->>JWTManager: new signed token string
    JWTManager-->>Client: newTokenStr
